Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Allocator Visualization Module

Provides visualization tools for allocator state, usage, and fragmentation.

Features:
- Real-time visualization of allocator state and usage
- Fragmentation and leak visualization
- Integration with developer dashboards and IDEs
- Extensible hooks for custom visualizations
- AI/agent-friendly visualization APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note


Import "../utilities/common" as Common
Note: Allocator Visualization Types and Interfaces
Type called "AllocatorVisualizer":
    visualize_state as Function that takes allocator as Allocator returns VisualizationData
    visualize_fragmentation as Function that takes allocator as Allocator returns VisualizationData
    export_dashboard as Function that takes data as VisualizationData returns None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VisualizationData":
    data as Any
    format as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Allocator Visualization Functions
Process called "visualize_state" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and allocator as Allocator returns VisualizationData:
    Note: Visualizes allocator state
    Return VisualizationData

Process called "visualize_fragmentation" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and allocator as Allocator returns VisualizationData:
    Note: Visualizes allocator fragmentation
    Return VisualizationData

Process called "export_dashboard" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and data as VisualizationData returns None:
    Note: Exports visualization to dashboard
    Return None 

Note: Live Interactive Visualization
Process called "start_live_dashboard" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and allocator as Allocator returns None:
    Note: Starts a live dashboard for allocator visualization
    While dashboard is active:
        Let data be visualizer.visualize_state(allocator)
        update_dashboard(data)
        wait for update_interval
    Return None

Process called "register_event_hook" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and event as String and handler as Function returns None:
    Note: Registers a handler for allocator events (allocation, deallocation, error)
    visualizer.event_hooks[event] = handler
    Return None

Process called "integrate_with_ide" that takes visualizer as AllocatorVisualizer and ide as DeveloperIDE returns None:
    Note: Integrates allocator visualization with developer IDE
    ide.register_visualization_tool(visualizer)
    Return None 